description:
&ldquo;You are invited to a challenge of nerves and maneuvers in the ultimate dare! Race against your friends through a terrifying graveyard where roaming Spirits emerge from their resting place to hinder your every step. Make your way in harried haste through the misty maze of standing stones and decaying dead. Play your cards with care, speed your way past the creeping corpses, and be the first to escape the realm of wraiths through the Lychgates!&rdquo;

On a game board of 121 spaces, there are 4 starting points and 4 goals (the Lychgates). There are also five points on the board which will spawn &ldquo;Spirits&rdquo; as the game progresses. By playing from a hand of movement cards, each player is racing across the board to one of two designated goals. Each player also has six special move-enhancing cards that they can play when they wish, and once all six have been used they are refreshed to be used again. In addition, the players can control the Spirits to hinder their opponents, blocking their way to the goals. As soon as a Spirit is moved, a new one will spawn in its place. As the game goes on, the board becomes inhabited by as many as 25 roaming spirits to be dealt with.

-description from designer

Choose your car, tire type, and rev up the engines in a race full of strategy and a dash of luck.

Between fuel management, car collisions, pit stops, and weather changes, you'll need to handle various unexpected events to outsmart your opponents.

The realistic board game, packed with all the excitement of Stock Car racing, accommodates 2 to 6 players per match and includes a simplified mode for playing with kids. Get ready for a thrilling race from start to finish, with plenty of twists and an unexpected podium!


     Plot the best course to gain speed;
     Pay attention to the weather forecast;
     Outperform opponents with the help of the radio, drafting, brakes, and fuel;
     Raise the trophy by winning the race at the checkered flag!


&mdash;description from the designer

&ldquo;You&rsquo;re old enough to visit the Dream Realms yourself now. This book is a DREAM PROJECTOR that will help us plan a dream together, that we&rsquo;ll explore tonight in our sleep! We&rsquo;ve been searching for someone to pass it on to &hellip; someone with a special talent for dreaming. Finally, we&rsquo;ve found you! Take good care of it. And may you always have dreams full of wonder, adventure, and magic!&rdquo;
-Lily & Ben

Many parents think they&rsquo;re terrible storytellers. So they don&rsquo;t tell stories at all. Luckily, you&rsquo;re holding in your hands not a book, but a BEDTIME STORY GENERATOR. In A Guide to Dream Travel, gorgeous pages filled with story prompts let even the most exhausted parent tell fantastical tales to (and better yet, with) their children at bedtime.

A monster will come to kidnap you for a week starting tomorrow night. If you hide an important red object as a talisman, monsters will not come near you. If they see you, the monsters will catch you and take you away. Be careful&hellip;

Secret Red is a trick-taking game whose flavor is one of the monster legends passed down in medieval Europe. Although it is simple, it seems to have high replayability. Blue 13 and yellow 7 are in play, and it's your turn. The cards that can be played are the must-follow Blue 11, Blue 5, and the trump card Red 8. Which one would you like to serve?
If you are aiming for a red 8 and the winner of the round, if the 4th player has a red 10, it will be painful if it is played. (Get 10+8+2=20 points. Each non-red card gets 1 point.) The fact that there is something to think about in each round is probably the reason why it is interesting and highly replayable.

You find yourself in a cold, post-apocalyptic world where the stench of rotting potato skin fills the air. Just when you thought you had survived contamination, you see the undead coming for you&hellip;

That's right, Toxic Potato is back with an expansion pack that pits survivors against their contaminated friends. A cast of undead characters, like King Tot and the Headless Horseyam, will work together to contaminate every last player left in the game.

Survivors will have to decide to work as a team to take out the undead or look out for themselves and try to remain the sole survivor. Either way, in this expansion pack, everyone is always in the game because contamination is just the beginning&hellip;

&mdash;description from the designer

Twirls of Action is played on a 9x9 or 8x8 Go board.

The game has same starting set up as the Classic Lines of Action, and the end goal is almost the same as well.

A player wins when they connects all of their stones, where each stone does not have more than three adjacent (diagonal or orthogonal) friendly stones.

From The World of Abstract Games:

MOVE - Each stone move by a Twirl movement. This is done on the following steps:
    Select an enemy stone as the Pivot (at a distance of N cells);
    The Pivot must be on a straight line (diagonal or orthogonal) without any other stone in-between;
    The stone can go another empty cell at the distance of N cells from the Pivot;
    The origin and the destiny cell must be on a straight line (diagonal or orthogonal) without any other stone in-between;

